race.comment: The well-bred JOISELLE (6) resumes and brings strong provincial and metro form. Has won 2/3 fresh and has trialled well. Has an inside gate and 2x winning rider Nock is booked. Won her only start at the track and everything points to a bold return. SPECK (3) won this grade comfortably at Tamworth and then wasn't beaten far in Open company at Dubbo. Maps well and also has strong claims. WAVE BREAKER (5) has switched from the Snowden yard on a 40-day return. Her effort at Kembla Grange two back reads well for this and she has to be kept very safe. ZOE SHARK (1) built on the in this grade with a near miss in a 64 at Newcastle. Has been freshened and can't entirely be ruled out.
